 <H1>Comments on ISAM</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>File creation:  Leaf (data) pages allocated                  sequentially, sorted by search key; then index        pages allocated, then space for overflow pages.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Index entries:  <search key value, page id>;  they   `direct’ search for data entries, which are in leaf pages.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Search:  Start at root; use key comparisons to go to leaf.  Cost     log F N ; F = # entries/index pg, N = # leaf pgs
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Insert:  Find leaf data entry belongs to, and put it there.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Delete:  Find and remove from leaf; if empty overflow page, de-allocate. </H2></P>

<P></UL></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI> Static tree structure:  inserts/deletes affect only leaf pages.</UL></P>

